  <p>
    In order to multiply a fraction by a whole number such as <m>4</m>, just remember that <m>4</m> can be written as <m>\frac{4}{1}</m>.  For example, we have
    <me>
      4\cdot \frac{2}{5}=\frac{4}{1}\cdot\frac{2}{5}=\frac{8}{5}.
    </me>
  </p>

